        <p>Drug-treats-disease probability predicts the probability that a given drug can treat a given disease. We developed this computational drug repurposing approach based on the model framework proposed by <xref rid="btad082-B52" ref-type="bibr">Womack <italic toggle="yes">et al.</italic> (2019)</xref>. In order to adapt this model to our core KG RTX-KG2, we modified the implementation of the model by replacing node2vec (<xref rid="btad082-B15" ref-type="bibr">Grover and Leskovec, 2016</xref>) with GraphSage (<xref rid="btad082-B16" ref-type="bibr">Hamilton <italic toggle="yes">et al.</italic>, 2017</xref>) for generating the node embeddings as well as using direct concatenation instead of the Hadamard product to generate the input features for a Random Forest classifier for drug–disease pairs. Additional performance gains may be realized through the use of alternative embedding or prediction models, though Section 3.3 indicates the current approach performs favorably.</p>
